# Bits UI

**Opt-in only.** This rule applies when you @-mention it (or the user explicitly asks for Bits UI). Do not add Bits UI for simple UI — plain HTML + Tailwind is fine for static layout, links, basic forms, and one-off buttons.

Reach for Bits UI when the task needs headless primitives: dialogs, menus, popovers, comboboxes, tabs, tooltips, etc. — especially keyboard/focus/ARIA behavior you'd otherwise hand-roll.

## Usage

- Import from `"bits-ui"` — e.g. `import { Dialog } from "bits-ui"`
- Style with Tailwind via `class` prop on each part (`.Root`, `.Trigger`, `.Content`, …)
- Build reusable styled wrappers in `src/lib/components/ui/`; pages compose those, not raw Bits primitives
- Ignore demo classnames in Bits docs unless relevant to the task

## Custom elements

Use the `child` snippet when you need scoped styles, transitions, or a custom element:

```svelte
<Dialog.Trigger>
	{#snippet child({ props })}
		<button {...props} class="btn">Open</button>
	{/snippet}
</Dialog.Trigger>
```

Always spread `{...props}`. For floating content (Popover, Select, Dialog, Tooltip, …): two-level structure with `{...wrapperProps}` on the outer element and `{...props}` on the inner — never style the wrapper.

## Docs (before implementing a component)

1. Index: https://bits-ui.com/llms.txt
2. Per component: `https://bits-ui.com/docs/components/{component}/llms.txt`
3. Core guides: [child-snippet](https://bits-ui.com/docs/child-snippet/llms.txt), [styling](https://bits-ui.com/docs/styling/llms.txt)

Date/time components require `@internationalized/date` (add when first used).

## Do not

- Add another UI component library without explicit request
- Use legacy Svelte 4 slot/event patterns with Bits UI (see `svelte.mdc`)
